Class ExpressionRenderer

java.lang.Object
  prefuse.render.AbstractShapeRenderer
      diagrams.ExpressionRenderer
All Implemented Interfaces:
prefuse.render.Renderer
public class ExpressionRenderer
extends prefuse.render.AbstractShapeRenderer

This class extends prefuse's AbstractShapeRenderer to represent microarray grids, allowing the distortion of the size of rows and columns

Author:
Rodrigo Santamaria

Constructor Detail

ExpressionRenderer

public ExpressionRenderer(int numRows,
                          int numCols,
                          double totalHeight,
                          double totalWidth)
Creates a new ExpressionRenderer with given number of rows, columns and maximum size for the whole diagram.

Parameters:
numRows - the number of rows in the microarray heatmap checkerboard structure
numCols - the number of columns in the microarray heatmap checkerboard structure
totalHeight - total height of the diagram. Initially, each square will hava a height of totalHeight/numRows
totalWidth - total width of the diagram. Initially, each square will hava a width of totalWidth/numRows
Method Detail

getRawShape

public java.awt.Shape getRawShape(prefuse.visual.VisualItem item)
Returns an square of the adequate dimensions for an item. It takes field "colId" and "rowId" from the VisualItem to determine the position of the square in the heatmap and thus assign to it width and height

Specified by:
getRawShape in class prefuse.render.AbstractShapeRenderer
